# Final check for density and connectivity:
# Every entity should be linked to at least one other.
# Resources are linked to Agents, ProductModels, Locations, Applications, NetworkInterfaces.
# NetworkInterfaces are linked to Resources and NetworkLinks.
# NetworkLinks are linked to NetworkInterfaces and Resources.
# Applications are linked to Resources and ApplicationModules.
# ApplicationModules are linked to Applications and Agents/OrgUnits.
# Services are linked to Applications/ApplicationModules/Resources.
# TroubleTickets are linked to Services/Applications/Resources, Agents, EventRecords.
# TroubleTicketNotes are linked to TroubleTickets and Agents.
# ChangeRequests are linked to Resources/Applications/Services, Agents, EventRecords.
# EventRecords are linked to Resources/Applications, Agents, ManagementSystems (Applications), TroubleTickets/ChangeRequests.
# OperationPlans are linked to ActionPre/PostConditions.
# ActionPre/PostConditions are linked to OperationPlans.
# Agents are linked to OrgUnits, and manage Resources/Applications/TroubleTickets/ChangeRequests.
# OrgUnits are linked to other OrgUnits and contain Agents.
# ProductModels are linked to Organizations.
# Sites are linked to Rooms.
# Rooms are linked to Loci.
# Loci are linked to Resources.

# This structure ensures a high degree of connectivity and density, covering various aspects of IT operations and incident management.
# The number of entities and properties used should be sufficient to meet the token count requirement.
